must gain mettle, oh fledgling.

106
00:10:41,319 --> 00:10:42,822
{\an1}Who are you?

107
00:10:42,855 --> 00:10:46,493
{\an1}'Tis quite precise
question for this place
but...

108
00:10:46,526 --> 00:10:51,166
{\an1}I am quite uneasy over
whether thou shalt be able
to connect my name with my

109
00:10:51,200 --> 00:10:53,402
{\an1}actions as a herald...

110
00:10:54,170 --> 00:10:55,239
Uh--

111
00:10:56,073 --> 00:10:59,311
{\an1}I am he who shall achieve
peace and order...

112
00:10:59,343 --> 00:11:01,546
{\an1}And my name is Hagoromo.

113
00:11:08,223 --> 00:11:09,959
{\an1}But on the other hand...

114
00:11:09,992 --> 00:11:15,299
{\an1}I had already foreseen that
thou wouldst end up in such
a state as that one, after all.

115
00:11:15,900 --> 00:11:20,839
{\an1}<i>Uh... I don't really</i>
<i>understand what he's</i>
<i>saying... He seems to be one</i>

116
00:11:20,873 --> 00:11:22,709
{\an1}<i>of those annoying geezers! </i>

117
00:11:24,879 --> 00:11:28,016
{\an1}Hey... Sorry,
gramps, but I--

118
00:11:28,049 --> 00:11:29,184
Now then...

119
00:11:29,217 --> 00:11:30,786
{\an1}No way! Those eyes!

120
00:11:30,820 --> 00:11:32,388
{\an1}Rinnegan!

121
00:11:32,889 --> 00:11:36,693
{\an1}Thou dost appear to possess
observant eyes.

122
00:11:36,728 --> 00:11:41,700
{\an1}All that remains is for thee
to pragmatically comprehend
thy circumstances...

123
00:11:41,734 --> 00:11:47,209
{\an1}Firstly, thou hast not died
as of yet... This place is
thine own inner mind.

124
00:11:47,242 --> 00:11:48,710
{\an1}I understand thine haste--

125
00:11:48,744 --> 00:11:53,716
{\an7}<i>This geezer's not an</i>
<i>enemy... But...</i>

126
00:11:53,750 --> 00:11:58,290
{\an7}Look, a lot simpler, please!
Can't you just speak using
easy, normal words?!

127
00:11:58,324 --> 00:12:00,793
{\an1}Forgive me. I'm an
anachronism.

128
00:12:00,826 --> 00:12:06,034
{\an1}Over the passage of much
time, cultural traditions
and notions, ethics, have

129
00:12:06,067 --> 00:12:09,204
{\an1}managed to bring about some
rather significant changes.

130
00:12:09,738 --> 00:12:14,345
{\an7}<i>In each instance where I</i>
<i>cross time and meet a</i>
<i>reincarnate, I have come to</i>

